      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">What is OCR?</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-6">OCR stands for <strong>Optical Character Recognition</strong>. It's a technology that reads text from images — whether those images are photos of documents, screenshots of web pages, or scans of handwritten notes. The OCR engine analyzes the pixels, identifies letter shapes, and converts them into editable, searchable text.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Common Use Cases for OCR</h2>
      <ul class="text-muted-foreground space-y-2 mb-6">
        <li>📄 <strong>Digitizing scanned documents</strong> — convert paper documents to editable text</li>
        <li>📸 <strong>Screenshots to text</strong> — copy text from images, infographics, or locked PDFs</li>
        <li>🧾 <strong>Receipt scanning</strong> — extract amounts and vendor names for expense tracking</li>
        <li>📚 <strong>Book digitization</strong> — convert photographed book pages to searchable text</li>
        <li>🌍 <strong>Translation prep</strong> — extract foreign-language text for translation tools</li>
        <li>📋 <strong>Data entry</strong> — extract tables and structured data from images</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Why Browser-Based OCR is Better</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">Most OCR tools require you to upload your images to a remote server. This raises serious privacy concerns, especially for:</p>
      <ul class="text-muted-foreground space-y-2 mb-6">
        <li>🔒 Medical records and prescriptions</li>
        <li>🔒 Financial documents and tax forms</li>
        <li>🔒 Legal contracts and court documents</li>
        <li>🔒 Personal ID cards and passports</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-6">ToolGrid's OCR runs <strong>100% locally in your browser</strong> using Tesseract.js (a WebAssembly port of the world's most accurate open-source OCR engine). Your images are never transmitted anywhere.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Supported Languages</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-6">Our OCR tool supports 100+ languages out of the box, including English, Hindi, Spanish, French, German, Chinese (Simplified & Traditional), Japanese, Korean, Arabic, Russian, Portuguese, and many more.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Tips for Better OCR Results</h2>
      <ul class="text-muted-foreground space-y-2 mb-6">
        <li>📷 Use <strong>high-resolution images</strong> — blurry photos produce poor results</li>
        <li>💡 Ensure <strong>good lighting</strong> and contrast</li>
        <li>📐 Keep the text <strong>straight and aligned</strong> — skewed text reduces accuracy</li>
        <li>🖊️ <strong>Printed text</strong> works better than handwriting (though handwriting is improving)</li>
      </ul>

